# Go backend (`apps/backend`)

For **lint, tests, and local restart**, follow the always-on workflow rule (`quokkaq-agent-workflow.mdc`). This rule covers **architecture and style** only.

## Stack

- Module: `quokkaq-go-backend` · Go 1.26.2+
- HTTP: Chi v5 · Auth: JWT · DB: PostgreSQL + GORM · Jobs: Asynq · Real-time: Gorilla WebSocket · Storage: AWS SDK v2 (S3/MinIO)

## Layering

Use the existing flow: **handlers → services → repository → models**. Extend nearby patterns for errors, HTTP status codes, and JSON responses instead of introducing parallel trees.

- Entry and route registration: [`apps/backend/cmd/api/main.go`](apps/backend/cmd/api/main.go)
- Deeper context: [`apps/backend/AGENTS.md`](apps/backend/AGENTS.md)

## New HTTP API surface

1. Wire routes in `main.go`.
2. Add Swagger annotations on handlers; regenerate docs when contracts change: `swag init -g cmd/api/main.go -o ./docs` (CI checks OpenAPI artifacts — see [`.github/workflows/ci.yml`](.github/workflows/ci.yml)).

## Configuration

- New env vars: document in [`apps/backend/.env.example`](apps/backend/.env.example).
- Default API port in dev: **3001**.

